<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.001 Orellana, Manuel/2</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Guatemalan Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Recinos</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation<note n="4" xml:id="d137fn4">Translation supplied by the editors.</note>]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-18">December 18, 1930</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 103</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Under instructions from the
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs of Guatemala, I have the honor to inform
                            Your Excellency that, by virtue of the resignation of Licentiate don
                            Baudilio Palma, the Legislative Assembly in yesterday’s session named
                            General Manuel Orellana as Acting President of the Republic during the
                            illness of General Lázaro Chacón.</p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adrián Recinos</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>